# CODEOWNERS — TrottiStore
#
# Defines mandatory reviewers for security- and stability-critical paths.
# Combined with branch protection rules on `main` (require pull request
# review from code owners), any PR touching these paths is blocked until an
# owner has explicitly approved it.
#
# Rationale: the AUDIT_METHODOLOGY.md layer 7 (human review) and the
# NIST SSDF PO.1 (maintained security requirements) both require that
# changes to sensitive code paths are reviewed by a designated owner,
# not merged by whoever opened the PR.
#
# Ordering matters: later patterns override earlier ones. The last
# matching pattern takes precedence.
#
# Docs:
#   https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
